<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 12:57:46 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>一些技术利用加速的自然过程来捕获碳，但它们能持久地储存碳吗？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/some-technologies-use-accelerated-natural-processes-to-capture-carbon-but-can-they-store-it-durably</link><description>数百万年来，自然地质过程一直在调节地球的气候。这些过程的加速版本现在正在作为从大气中吸收碳的技术得到推广，其中一些正在迅速从概念转向现实世界的部署。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/some-technologies-use-accelerated-natural-processes-to-capture-carbon-but-can-they-store-it-durably2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 12:57:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/some-technologies-use-accelerated-natural-processes-to-capture-carbon-but-can-they-store-it-durably</guid></item><item><title>埃里克·施密特 (Eric Sc​​hmidt) 警告：“你不知道 2027 年会发生什么”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/eric-schmidt-warns-you-have-no-idea-whats-coming-in-2027</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 12:42:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/eric-schmidt-warns-you-have-no-idea-whats-coming-in-2027</guid></item><item><title>Glasswing 项目：初始更新</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/project-glasswing-an-initial-update</link><description>我们从 Glasswing 项目中学到的知识的早期更新。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/project-glasswing-an-initial-update2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 12:27:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/project-glasswing-an-initial-update</guid></item><item><title>像康宁柳玻璃一样弯曲它</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/bend-it-like-corning-willow-glass</link><description>CNET 的 Jessica Dolcourt 为您带来了一款像名片一样薄的新型可弯曲玻璃的独家抢先体验。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/bend-it-like-corning-willow-glass.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 12:12:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/bend-it-like-corning-willow-glass</guid></item><item><title>线粒体作为细胞信号传导的来源和靶标</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/mitochondria-as-sources-and-targets-of-cellular-signaling</link><description>梅克斯纳等人。回顾最近对线粒体作为动态信号中枢的见解。作者描述了结构可塑性和细胞间通讯如何使线粒体充当信号传导的来源和目标，协调应激反应、代谢适应和先天免疫途径，以维护细胞稳态。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/mitochondria-as-sources-and-targets-of-cellular-signaling.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 11:57:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/mitochondria-as-sources-and-targets-of-cellular-signaling</guid></item><item><title>消除量子噪声</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/canceling-quantum-noise</link><description>一项新技术使用“抗噪声”信号来消除与精密测量（例如引力波探测所需的测量）相关的不可避免的量子噪声。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/canceling-quantum-noise.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 11:42:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/canceling-quantum-noise</guid></item><item><title>超导涡旋作为可控量子位，将破坏转化为资源</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/superconducting-vortices-moonlight-as-controllable-qubits-turning-a-disruption-into-a-resource</link><description>迄今为止，超导体中的涡流被认为是一种破坏，因为它们会损害超导性能。卡尔斯鲁厄理工学院（KIT）的研究人员在实验中证明，磁涡旋可以在某些材料中用作可控量子系统。这意味着以前不需要的现象正在成为量子技术的潜在资源，为量子计算机、高灵敏度传感器系统和材料研究创新方法的发展开辟了新途径。这些结果是&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/superconducting-vortices-moonlight-as-controllable-qubits-turning-a-disruption-into-a-resource.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 11:27:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/superconducting-vortices-moonlight-as-controllable-qubits-turning-a-disruption-into-a-resource</guid></item><item><title>为什么轴子暗物质的内在量子效应是完全无法检测到的</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/why-the-intrinsic-quantum-effects-of-axion-dark-matter-are-completely-undetectable</link><description>暗物质是一种难以捉摸的物质形式，几乎从不发射、吸收或反射光，只与常规物质发生微弱的相互作用。这些特性使得使用传统的实验技术和仪器很难检测到。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/why-the-intrinsic-quantum-effects-of-axion-dark-matter-are-completely-undetectable.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 11:12:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/why-the-intrinsic-quantum-effects-of-axion-dark-matter-are-completely-undetectable</guid></item><item><title>人工智能在困扰专家数十年的数学问题上取得重大突破</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-makes-a-major-breakthrough-in-a-math-problem-that-had-stumped-experts-for-decades</link><description>近 80 年来，数学家们一直在努力解决 Paul Erdős 于 1946 年首次提出的经典几何难题：平面单位距离问题。这位匈牙利传奇数学家提出的问题表面上看似简单。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-makes-a-major-breakthrough-in-a-math-problem-that-had-stumped-experts-for-decades.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 10:57:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-makes-a-major-breakthrough-in-a-math-problem-that-had-stumped-experts-for-decades</guid></item><item><title>天文学家发现一颗超级地球围绕附近的红矮星运行</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/astronomers-discover-a-super-earth-orbiting-a-nearby-red-dwarf</link><description>来自意大利和巴西的天文学家调查了附近一颗名为罗斯 318 的红矮星，并发现了一颗围绕这颗恒星运行的系外行星，其质量至少是地球的六倍。研究论文报告了这一发现&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/astronomers-discover-a-super-earth-orbiting-a-nearby-red-dwarf2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 23 May 2026 10:42:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/astronomers-discover-a-super-earth-orbiting-a-nearby-red-dwarf</guid></item></channel></rss>